<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1155,142,237]" box="[160,409,142,168]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,409,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">External morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1155,142,237]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Body rounded, flat; light red, with two dark circles on dorsum; yellow-brown line present at laterals of body next to the first circle. Gills light red, white at tips of branchial leaves.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="273" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1155,281,377]" box="[160,252,281,307]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,281,307]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1155,281,377]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
A single specimen was found at a shallow depth under a rock, on top of the sponge 
<taxonomicName authority="Vacelet and Perez, 2008" authorityName="Vacelet and Perez" authorityYear="2008" box="[160,620,352,377]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Phorbas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti">
<emphasis box="[160,342,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Phorbas topsenti</emphasis>
Vacelet and Pérez, 2008
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="273" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,420,516]" box="[160,300,420,446]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,420,446]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,420,516]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
Atlantic Spanish coast: 
<collectingRegion box="[429,592,456,481]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pruvot-Fol A" box="[609,792,456,481]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref21976" refString="Pruvot-Fol A. 1953. Etude de quelques Opisthobranches de la cote Atlantique du Maroc et du Senegal. Travaux de l'Institut Scientifique Cherifien. 5: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1953">Pruvot-Fol 1953</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pruvot-Fol" authorityYear="1953" box="[841,1010,456,481]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cadlinidae" genus="Aldisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="binotata">
<emphasis box="[841,1010,456,481]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Aldisa binotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ortea J &amp; Perez JM &amp; Llera EM" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref21704" refString="Ortea J, Perez JM, Llera EM. 1982. Moluscos opistobranquios recolectados durante el plan de bentos circuncanario. Cuadernos del CRINAS. 3: 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1982">Ortea et al. 1982</bibRefCitation>
); Mediterranean Spanish coast: 
<collectingRegion box="[574,679,491,516]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Catalonia</collectingRegion>
(this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,559,828]" box="[160,262,559,585]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,559,585]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1156,559,828]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">
In the original description the body was described as red with two large dark circles and a white line just after the first dark circle (
<bibRefCitation author="Ortea J &amp; Perez JM &amp; Llera EM" box="[611,793,630,655]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref21704" refString="Ortea J, Perez JM, Llera EM. 1982. Moluscos opistobranquios recolectados durante el plan de bentos circuncanario. Cuadernos del CRINAS. 3: 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1982">Ortea et al. 1982</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen studied here has lighter red colouration and lacks the second dark circle. The gills are also light red and white on the top, while the conspecific 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pruvot-Fol, 1951)" baseAuthorityName="Pruvot-Fol" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[599,956,699,724]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cadlinidae" genus="Aldisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="banyulensis">
<emphasis box="[599,752,699,724]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">A. banyulensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pruvot-Fol A" box="[764,949,699,724]" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref21948" refString="Pruvot-Fol A. 1951. Etude des Nudibranches de la Mediterranee (2 e partie). Archs Zool Exp Gen. 88: 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1951">Pruvot-Fol, 1951</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
has dark red gills, lacking the white top. Moreover, our specimen has a yellow line in the anterior part of the body, anterior to the first dot, while in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pruvot-Fol" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[589,742,768,793]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cadlinidae" genus="Aldisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="8" pageNumber="273" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="banyulensis">
<emphasis box="[589,742,768,793]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="273">A. banyulensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the yellow line is found between the first and second dots, displayed slightly towards the posterior part.
</paragraph>
